\s1 Daniel’s Development in the King’s Court
\m 
\v 1 In \add the\add* third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah, Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon came to Jerusalem and besieged it. 
\v 2 And the Lord gave Jehoiakim the king of Judah into his hand and ⸤some of⸥\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Literally “from the end/extremity/limits” \f* of the utensils of the temple of God,\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Hebrew “the God” \f* and he brought them \add to\add* the land of Shinar \add to\add* the temple of his gods, and he brought the utensils to ⸤the treasury⸥\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Literally “the house of the treasury” \f* of his gods.
\p 
\v 3 And the king ⸤ordered⸥\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Literally “said to” \f* Ashpenaz, the commander of his court officials, to bring ⸤some of the Israelites⸥\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Literally “from the sons/children of Israel” \f* from ⸤the royal family⸥\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Literally “from the seed of the kingship” \f* and from the lords,\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Or “nobles” \f* 
