\v 5 And the king assigned to them ⸤his daily portion⸥\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Literally “\fq the \ft portion of the day on its day” \f* from the fine food of the king, and from ⸤the wine that he drank⸥,\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Literally “the wine of his drink” \f* and \add instructed that\add* ⸤they were to be educated for three years⸥.\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Literally “and to be educated them years three” \f* And at the end \add of\add* their \add training\add*, ⸤they were to be stationed⸥\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Literally “they would stand” \f* ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Literally “to the face of” \f* the king. 
\v 6 Now there was among them ⸤from the Judeans⸥,\f + \fr 1:6 \ft Literally “from the children of Judah” \f* Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah. 
