\s1 Daniel’s Resolve
\m 
\v 8 Now ⸤Daniel resolved⸥\f + \fr 1:8 \ft Literally “Daniel placed upon his heart” \f* that he would not defile himself with the fine food of the king, and with ⸤the wine that he drank⸥,\f + \fr 1:8 \ft Literally “the wine of his drink” \f* and \add so\add* he requested from the commander of the court officials \add permission so\add* that he would not defile himself. 
\v 9 And God\f + \fr 1:9 \ft Hebrew “the God” \f* gave Daniel favor and compassion ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 1:9 \ft Literally “to the face of” \f* the commander of the court officials, 
\v 10 and the commander of the court officials said to Daniel, “I \add am\add* afraid \add of\add* my lord, the king, who has determined your food and your drink, for ⸤why should⸥\f + \fr 1:10 \ft Literally “to what would” \f* he see your face having a worse appearance than the young men who ⸤are your age⸥?\f + \fr 1:10 \ft Literally “like your age”; “your” is plural \f* Then you will endanger my head with the king.” 
\v 11 Then\f + \fr 1:11 \ft Hebrew “And” \f* Daniel asked the guard\f + \fr 1:11 \ft Or “overseer” \f* whom the commander of the court officials \add had\add* appointed over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah, 
