\c 2
\s1 The King’s Troubling Dream
\m 
\v 1 Now\f + \fr 2:1 \ft Hebrew “And” \f* in the second year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadnezzar dreamed dreams; and his spirit was troubled and his sleep left him. 
\v 2 So the king said to call the magicians\f + \fr 2:2 \ft Or “soothsayer-priests” \f* and the conjurers\f + \fr 2:2 \ft Or “enchanters” \f* and the sorcerers and the ⸤astrologers⸥\f + \fr 2:2 \ft Literally “Chaldeans” \f* to tell to the king his dreams. And they came in and they stood ⸤before⸥\f + \fr 2:2 \ft Literally “to the face of” \f* the king. 
\v 3 And the king said to them, “⸤I have had a dream⸥\f + \fr 2:3 \ft Literally “A dream I have dreamed” \f* and my spirit is anxious to know the dream.”
\p 
\v 4 And the ⸤astrologers⸥\f + \fr 2:4 \ft Literally “Chaldeans” \f* said to the king \add in\add* Aramaic,\f + \fr 2:4 \ft The text of Daniel is in Aramaic from this point on through Daniel chapter 7. Then the text resumes in Hebrew to the end of the book \f* “O king, live forever! Tell the dream to your servants and we will reveal the explanation.” 
\v 5 The king answered and said to the ⸤astrologers⸥,\f + \fr 2:5 \ft Literally “Chaldeans” \f* “The command from me is firm: if you \add do\add* not make known to me the dream and its explanation,\f + \fr 2:5 \ft Or “interpretation” \f* \add then\add* you will be broken into pieces and your houses will be laid in ruins. 
\v 6 But if you tell me the dream and its explanation, you will receive gifts and rewards\f + \fr 2:6 \ft Aramaic “reward” \f* and great honor from me. Therefore, tell me the dream and its explanation.”\f + \fr 2:6 \ft Or “interpretation” \f* 
\v 7 They answered once more and said, “Let the king tell the dream to his servants and we will make the explanation known.” 
\v 8 The king answered and said, “⸤Certainly⸥\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Literally “From \fq a \ft certainty” \f* I know that ⸤you are trying to gain time⸥\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Literally “the time you are gaining” \f* ⸤because⸥\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Literally “all because of that” \f* you have seen ⸤that this matter is firmly decreed by me⸥,\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Literally “that firm from me \fq is \ft the decree” \f* 
\v 9 for if you \add do\add* not make the dream known to me, ⸤your verdict is fixed⸥,\f + \fr 2:9 \ft Literally “one is your verdict” \f* and you have conspired to say \add a\add* lying and deceitful word to me until the ⸤circumstances⸥\f + \fr 2:9 \ft Literally “time” \f* will change. Therefore, tell me the dream, and I will know that you can tell me its explanation.” 
\v 10 The ⸤astrologers⸥\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Literally “Chaldeans” \f* answered the king and said, “There is not a man on earth that is able to reveal the word of the king; ⸤in fact⸥,\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Literally “all because that” \f* no great and powerful king has \add ever\add* asked a thing like this of any magician\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Or “soothsayer-priest” \f* or conjurer\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Or “enchanter” \f* or ⸤astrologer⸥.\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Literally “Chaldean” \f* 
\v 11 And the thing that the king is asking \add is too\add* difficult and ⸤there is no one who⸥\f + \fr 2:11 \ft Literally “there is not another” \f* can reveal it to the king except \add the\add* gods ⸤whose dwelling is not with mortals⸥.”\f + \fr 2:11 \ft Literally “concerning their dwelling is not with flesh” \f*
\p 
\v 12 Because of this the king became angry, and he became very much enraged, and he said \add that\add* all the wise men of Babylon \add are\add* to be destroyed. 
\v 13 And the decree was issued, and the wise men ⸤were on the verge of being executed⸥,\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Literally “were in the process of being killed” \f* and they searched for Daniel and his companions to be executed. 
\v 14 Then Daniel responded prudently and discretely to Arioch, the commander of the imperial guard of the king, who had gone out to execute the wise men of Babylon. 
\v 15 ⸤He asked⸥\f + \fr 2:15 \ft Literally “he answered” \f* and said to Arioch, the royal official of the king, “⸤Why⸥\f + \fr 2:15 \ft Literally “Over what” \f* is the decree from the king \add so\add* severe?” Then Arioch explained the matter\f + \fr 2:15 \ft Or “situation” \f* to Daniel. 
\v 16 And Daniel went in and requested from the king that he would give him time, and ⸤he would tell the king⸥\f + \fr 2:16 \ft Literally “to tell/reveal to the king” \f* the explanation.\f + \fr 2:16 \ft Or “interpretation” \f*
\p 
\v 17 Then Daniel went to his home, and he made the matter known to Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah, his companions, 
\v 18 and \add told them\add* to seek mercy ⸤from the God of heaven⸥\f + \fr 2:18 \ft Literally “from before the God of the heaven” \f* concerning this mystery, so that Daniel and his companions, along with the remainder of the wise men of Babylon, would not be killed.
\p 
\v 19 Then in a vision of the night the mystery was revealed to Daniel; then Daniel blessed the God of heaven.
\p 
