\v 19 “Then Daniel, whose name \add was\add* Belteshazzar, was distressed ⸤for some time⸥,\f + \fr 4:19 \ft Literally “for one hour” \f* and his thoughts disturbed him. The king answered and he said, ‘Belteshazzar, let the dream and its explanation not disturb you.’ Belteshazzar answered and said, ‘My lord, \add may\add* the dream and its explanation \add be\add* for \add those who\add* hate you and for your enemies. 
