\v 5 ⸤Immediately⸥\f + \fr 5:5 \ft Literally “In its the hour” \f* ⸤human fingers⸥\f + \fr 5:5 \ft Literally “fingers of \fq the \ft hand of a man” \f* appeared and they wrote ⸤opposite⸥\f + \fr 5:5 \ft Literally “to over against” \f* the lampstand on the plaster of the wall of the palace of the king, and the king was watching\f + \fr 5:5 \ft Or “gazing at” \f* the palm of the hand that was writing. 
\v 6 Then his face changed and his thoughts terrified him, and ⸤his hip joints gave way⸥\f + \fr 5:6 \ft Literally “the limbs of his hip became loose” \f* and ⸤his knees knocked together⸥.\f + \fr 5:6 \ft Literally “his knees this to this they knocked together” \f* 
\v 7 The king cried ⸤aloud⸥\f + \fr 5:7 \ft Literally “with strength” \f* to bring \add in\add* the conjurers,\f + \fr 5:7 \ft Or “enchanters” \f* the ⸤astrologers⸥\f + \fr 5:7 \ft Literally “Chaldeans” \f* and the diviners; the king ⸤spoke⸥\f + \fr 5:7 \ft Literally “answered” \f* and said to \add the\add* wise men of Babylon, “Any man that can read this writing and can tell me its explanation will be clothed \add in\add* purple and \add will have\add* \add a\add* necklace of gold \add hung\add* around his neck and he will rule \add as\add* third \add in authority\add* in the kingdom.” 
\v 8 Then all the wise men of the king came in, but they were not able to read the writing or to make known its explanation.\f + \fr 5:8 \ft Aramaic “the explanation/ interpretation” \f* 
\v 9 Then the king, Belshazzar, became greatly terrified, and ⸤his facial features⸥\f + \fr 5:9 \ft Literally “shining of his face” \f* changed upon him, and his lords\f + \fr 5:9 \ft Or “nobles” \f* were perplexed.
\p 
\v 10 Because of the words of the king and his lords,\f + \fr 5:10 \ft Or “nobles” \f* the queen came into ⸤the banqueting hall⸥\f + \fr 5:10 \ft Literally “the house of the drinking” \f* and the queen ⸤spoke up⸥\f + \fr 5:10 \ft Literally “answered” \f* and said, “O king, live ⸤forever⸥,\f + \fr 5:10 \ft Literally “to eternity” \f* and let not your thoughts terrify you and \add do\add* not let your facial expressions ⸤grow pale⸥.\f + \fr 5:10 \ft Literally “change” \f* 
\v 11 There is a man in your kingdom ⸤who has the spirit of the holy gods in him⸥.\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Literally “who \fq the \ft spirit of holy gods \fq is \ft in him” \f* And in the days of your ⸤predecessor⸥,\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Literally “father” \f* enlightenment and insight and wisdom like the wisdom of the gods was found in him; and, O king, Nebuchadnezzar your ⸤predecessor⸥\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Literally “father” \f* appointed him \add as\add* chief of the magicians,\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Or “soothsayer-priests” \f* the conjurers,\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Or “enchanters” \f* the ⸤astrologers⸥,\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Literally “Chaldeans” \f* \add and\add* the diviners. Your ⸤predecessor⸥\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Literally “father” \f* the king \add did this\add* 
\v 12 ⸤because⸥\f + \fr 5:12 \ft Literally “all of because that” \f* \add there\add* was found in him \add an\add* excellent spirit and understanding and insight \add for\add* interpreting dreams and explaining riddles and solving riddles; \add that is\add*, in Daniel ⸤whom the king named⸥\f + \fr 5:12 \ft Literally “whom the king gave his name” \f* Belteshazzar. Now, let Daniel be called and he will tell the explanation.”\f + \fr 5:12 \ft Or “interpretation” \f*
\s1 Daniel Deciphers and Interprets the Writing
\m 
